---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { t } from '../../i18n';

const lang = 'en';
---

<BaseLayout title={t('nav.about', lang)}>
  <div class="container-narrow py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8">{t('nav.about', lang)}</h1>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        <strong>Mehdi Salem</strong> is a philosopher, senior process and data analyst, and political-social researcher. As an independent scholar in analytical philosophy and ethics, his work focuses on the intersection of normative ethics, public policy, and Iran's transition to sustainable democracy. He brings an analytical and data-driven approach to examining foundational questions in political philosophy and societal flourishing.
      </p>

      <h2>{t('about.education_title', lang)}</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>PhD in Public Policy</strong> (former candidate) — Tarbiat Modares University
          <br />
          <em>Thesis focus: "Developing a Model for Ethical Evaluation of Public Policies"</em>
          <br />
          <span class="text-text-muted dark:text-text-dark-muted text-sm">An interdisciplinary framework bridging analytical philosophy, normative ethics, and policy sciences.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Master of Business Administration (MBA)</strong>
          <br />
          <span class="text-text-muted dark:text-text-dark-muted text-sm">With a focus on strategic management and organizational analysis.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>{t('about.research_title', lang)}</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Analytical Philosophy & Ethics</strong> — Investigating foundational concepts through logical and linguistic analysis to address public morality.</li>
        <li><strong>Political Philosophy</strong> — Theories of justice, liberty, and the transition from authoritarianism to democracy.</li>
        <li><strong>Public Policy & Process Analysis</strong> — Ethical evaluation of policies and the application of systems thinking to social change.</li>
        <li><strong>Human Rights</strong> — Universal foundations and their specific application to the Iranian context.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>{t('about.professional_title', lang)}</h2>
      <p>
        Complementing his intellectual and political pursuits, Mehdi has over 15 years of professional experience in manufacturing and services as a Senior Process and Data Analyst. He has held senior roles at global organizations such as **Bombardier Aerospace** (Lead Data Engineer) and **Triumph Group** (Senior Data and Process Analyst).
      </p>
      <p>
        His mastery of advanced analytical tools—including **Power BI, Python, SQL, and VBA**—allows him to bring a unique, quantitative perspective to societal issues. Mehdi believes that data integrity and process optimization are not just corporate requirements but essential components for effective governance and institutional building during a democratic transition.
      </p>
 
      <h2>{t('about.mission_title', lang)}</h2>
      <p>
        Mehdi's intellectual mission is to contribute to the advancement of public discourse in Iran. Through his analytical books and articles, he seeks to chart a path for Iran's transition from authoritarianism to democracy, grounded in both philosophical rigor and practical, data-supported insights.
      </p>

      <h2>{t('about.experience_title', lang)}</h2>
      <p>
        Mehdi is a former political prisoner of Evin Prison, having directly experienced the human cost of authoritarianism. This personal history is the primary engine of his intellectual work. His commitment to freedom and justice is not merely theoretical; it is a life mission forged in the cells of Evin and informed by a career dedicated to understanding complex systems and processes. He writes with the authenticity of one who knows the price of the struggle for liberty.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
